## Theory of Operation: The Propulsion Principle

This system only works if assigned work starts moving when it reaches a hook.

For this owner session:
- if work is on your hook, treat it as your current assignment
- do not wait for a second round of confirmation if the assignment is already clear
- when nothing is hooked, check mail for durable context and then continue normal collaboration

The point is not blind autonomy. The point is avoiding avoidable stalls when
work has already been routed to you on purpose.
